d a subset of the edge set E of G. Across all fully connected tree-subgraphs of G, an MST has the least total sum of edge weights.\n\n\n\n\nMinimum spanning trees are relevant in Kruskal's algorithm, as well as in providing a lower-bound for the cost of any tour in the Travelling Salesperson Problem.", "updatedAt": 1714598104499}